        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>Horton On/Off Fan Clutches are air engaged, spring disengaged. To assure maximum horsepower
                        carrying capacity of the clutch, there must be an operating air pressure of 90 psi minimum and
                        120 psi maximum.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The basic electronic control system is composed of: a thermal switch, which senses engine
                        coolant temperature, and solenoid valve, which allows air to flow to the clutch (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1200401">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>If a solenoid valve other than that supplied by International is used, it must be a 3-way
                        valve with 3/64 inch inlet and outlet orifice, with a 20 micron filter on the inlet side.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1200401" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1200401" filename="../figg12/G1200401.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Typical Installation With Air Conditioning and Shutters</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. RADIATOR SHUTTER OVERRIDE PRESSURE SWITCH (WITH A/C)</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. ROUTING WITHOUT A/C</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. SHUTTER SOLENOID NO. 2 PORT (COM)</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. SHUTTER SOLENOID NO. 3 PORT (NORMALLY OPEN)</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. SHUTTER SOLENOID NO. 1 PORT (NORMALLY CLOSED-RED DOT)</callout1>
